<p>I found the following code for turning hex string to byte:</p>  <pre><code>      private static byte[] h2b(String hex)   {         int len = hex.length();         byte[] data = new byte[len / 2];         for (int i = 0; i &lt; len; i += 2) {             data[i / 2] = (byte) ((Character.digit(hex.charAt(i), 16) &lt;&lt; 4)                                  + Character.digit(hex.charAt(i+1), 16));         }         return data;   } </code></pre>  <p>My problem is that i am using an old java version and i can't use Character.digit . Is there an alternative to it?</p>